{"published time": "2024-03-04T16-18-99", "images": ["https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/428644021_795049532655289_8436791950823372872_n.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/428639078_795049565988619_3564969096314584780_n-e1709561614390.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/428641145_795049542655288_7439752274806321921_n.jpg"], "content": "<div class=\"single-content\"><figure class=\"post-thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"1198\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-04T16-18-99/000000.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-04T16-18-99/000000.jpg\" width=\"1800\"/></figure><!-- .post-thumbnail --><p><strong>The Armed Forces of Canada showed how Canadian servicemen in the UK teach Ukrainian sappers of mine method.</strong></p><p>About this<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CAFwithUkraine/posts/pfbid02U2vCGyHhv8JUsBHML9WCL6i7Xjvr6MnxCNsuaRtywgNuodSThtNxUh1DnWFugTKKl\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">inform</a>Canada's armed forces.</p><p>\u201cMines and other explosive objects pose a constant danger on a modern battlefield. To help save lives, Canada's armed forces stationed in the UK as part of a UNifayer surgery teach the warriors of the Armed Forces of Ukraine how to identify, avoid and neutralize these dangers, \u201dthe message reads.</p><div class=\"fotorama--wp\" data-auto=\"false\" data-captiontag=\"dd\" data-columns=\"0\" data-icontag=\"dt\" data-ids=\"547654,547652\" data-itemtag=\"dl\" data-link=\"file\" data-max-width=\"100%\" data-ratio=\"0.86811594202899\" data-size=\"large\" data-width=\"599\"><div class=\"gallery galleryid-547651 gallery-columns-0 gallery-size-thumbnail\" id=\"gallery-1\"><dl class=\"gallery-item\"><dt class=\"gallery-icon portrait\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-04T16-18-99/000001.jpg\" srcse